{
  "name": "Menu Order Push Notifications",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 📋 Menu Order Push Notifications\n\n📖 **Full documentation:**\nhttps://paoloronco.notion.site/Documentation-Menu-website-receive-notification-from-orders-32ef0ba27c3280acb9b0f8241a9292f7\n\n**What this workflow does:**\n- Your menu website sends customer orders to the `Webhook` node\n- n8n receives the order and forwards it to your ntfy topic\n- Every device connected to ntfy can receive the push notification\n\n**Setup overview:**\n1. Open the `Webhook` node and copy the **Production URL**\n2. In `website-mockup/menu-data.js`, set `orderWebhook` to that webhook URL\n3. Deploy the menu website: it must send every order to that exact webhook endpoint\n4. Deploy ntfy by following `docs/01-setup-ntfy.md`\n5. Create the ntfy admin user/password with:\n   `docker exec -e NTFY_PASSWORD=\"your_password\" ntfy ntfy user add --role=admin admin`\n6. Generate the token used by n8n with:\n   `docker exec ntfy ntfy token add admin`\n7. In n8n create a `Header Auth` credential:\n   Name: `HeaderAuth ntfy`\n   Value: `Bearer YOUR_NTFY_TOKEN`\n8. Open the `ntfy notification` node and replace `YOUR_TOPIC` in the URL\n9. Activate the workflow\n\n**Receive notifications on your devices:**\n- Install the **ntfy** app on Android or iPhone/iPad\n- Add your ntfy server URL inside the app\n- Log in with the username/password created during ntfy setup\n- Subscribe to the same topic used in the `ntfy notification` node\n\nSee the `docs/` folder for the full step-by-step setup.",
        "height": 700,
        "width": 700
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [-500, -470],
      "id": "b1c2d3e4-f5a6-7890-bcde-f12345678901",
      "name": "Documentation"
    },
    {
